        "content": "In a CoinJoin, each participant signs only their own input. Alice's key never touches Bob's input — enforced by the wiring (zero edges connecting them).\n\nThe full BIP143 chain built here in the next iteration:\n  privkey → pubkey → HASH160 → scriptCode\n  → BIP143 preimage (10 fields)\n  → append SIGHASH_ALL\n  → double_sha256 → sighash\n  → sign_as_bitcoin_core_low_r\n  → witness assembly (sig + pubkey)\n\nEach lane is completely isolated.",
