        "content": "Output 0 = 690 000 sats\nOutput 1 = 690 000 sats\nEqual: true  →  Ambiguity set = 2\n\nAn analyst inspecting this transaction cannot determine:\n  — Which input funded which output\n  — Which output belongs to Alice vs Bob\n\nHeuristics that fail here:\n  • CIOH (Common Input Ownership) — suggests shared ownership, but that's wrong\n  • Change detection — both outputs are equal, neither looks like change\n  • Address clustering — links inputs together, but cannot follow outputs",
