        "title": "What Makes This Work",
        "content": "The privacy guarantee is structural, not computational.\n\nYou did not run a privacy function. You placed two equal-value outputs in G2. Equal outputs break the analyst's ability to apply heuristics.\n\nIn the full implementation, the cryptographic chain ensures:\n  • Alice signs only her input (key isolation)\n  • Bob signs only his input\n  • Neither can spend the other's UTXO\n  • The TX is invalid if either signature is wrong\n\nBut the privacy — the ambiguity — is simply the two equal numbers you chose in G2.",
